cyteNX\":\"6.1\",\"BloodRNAPlasmacytoidDCNX\":\"0.3\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"24.8\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"22.0\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"3.2\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"7.1\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"1.2\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"3.6\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"5.8\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"2.2\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"5.8\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"1.2\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"9.8\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"3.8\"}',NULL,'This gene is a proto-oncogene and encodes a nuclear phosphoprotein that plays a role in cell cycle progression, apoptosis and cellular transformation. The encoded protein forms a heterodimer with the related transcription factor MAX. This complex binds to the E box DNA consensus sequence and regulates the transcription of specific target genes. Amplification of this gene is frequently observed in numerous human cancers. Translocations involving this gene are associated with Burkitt lymphoma and multiple myeloma in human patients. There is evidence to show that translation initiates both from an upstream, in-frame non-AUG (CUG) and a downstream AUG start site, resulting in the production of two isoforms with distinct N-termini. [provided by RefSeq, Aug 2017]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (40,'EGFR','ERBB1 ERBB','epidermal growth factor receptor',1956,'EGFR_HUMAN','downstream','7p12',55019032,55207338,1,'HS_EGFR_2','NM_005228','NP_005219','12,885,591,955,307,800,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','Egfr;Mus musculus,Egfr;Rattus norvegicus,Egfr;Drosophila melanogaster,egfra;Danio rerio','Древнейший общий предок metazoa имел комплементарный EGFR рецептор и предполагаемый лиганд EGF, которые дуплицировались или терялись в ходе эволюции [1].','Рецептор эпидермального фактора роста (EGFR) — это многофункциональный преобразователь сигналов, консервативный в ходе эволюции. Он участвует в широком спектре клеточных процессов, таких как гибель клеткок, пролиферация, дифференциация, апоптоз, миграция [2 - обзор функций].','Прямые доказательства на не млекопитающих, Возрастные изменения экспрессии гена/активности белка у человека, Ассоциации гена с долголетием/фенотипом старения','Активация EGF рецептора LET-23 у C. elegans ассоциирована с увеличенной средней и максимальной продолжительностью жизни [3]. EGF путь регулирует различные пути, влияющие на процесс старения клеток [4 - обзор]. Количество белка EGFR значиельно снижено в коже взрослых (старше 65 лет) пациентов, по сравнению с молодыми (моложе 25 лет). Аналогичные результаты показаны для первичных кератиноцитов [5].','The last common metazoan ancestor had an initial complement of one EGFR and one putative EGF ligand, which was often expanded or lost during animal evolution [1].','The epidermal growth factor receptor (EGFR) is a versatile signal transducer that has been well conserved during evolution. It functions in a wide range of cellular processes including cell fate determination, proliferation, cell migration and apoptosis [2 - review on functions].','Activation of EGF receptor LET-23 in C. elegnas is associated with increased mean and maximum lifespan [3]. EGF pathway regulates various pathways leading to cell senescence [4 - review]. EGFR is significantly downregulated in aged (more than 65 years) skin in human patients compared to young (less than 25 years) and primary human keranocytes [5].','[1] 10.1038/srep28071, [2] 10.1016/s0960-9822(01)00167-1, [3] 10.1016/j.exger.2010.10.010, [4] 10.18632/aging.100384 [5] 10.1007/s00520-016-3254-7',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614757146,3,'','',6,'ENSG00000146648','{\"Gene\":\"EGFR\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"ERBB\",\"ERBB1\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000146648\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Epidermal growth factor receptor\",\"Uniprot\":[\"P00533\"],\"Chromosome\":\"7\",\"Position\":\"55019021-55211628\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease related genes\",\"Enzymes\",\"FDA approved drug targets\",\"Plasma proteins\",\"Predicted intracellular proteins\",\"Predicted membrane proteins\",\"Predicted secreted proteins\",\"RAS pathway related proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":[\"Host-virus interaction\"],\"MolecularFunction\":[\"Developmental protein\",\"Host cell receptor for virus entry\",\"Kinase\",\"Receptor\",\"Transferase\",\"Tyrosine-protein kinase\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease mutation\",\"FDA approved drug targets\",\"Proto-oncogene\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Tissue enhanced\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":{\"Placenta\":\"102.3\"},\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Cell line enriched\",\"RNACellLineDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNACellLineSpecificityScore\":\"12\",\"RNACellLineSpecificNX\":{\"A431\":\"337.7\"},\"RNACancerSpecificity\":\"Cancer enhanced\",\"RNACancerDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNACancerSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNACancerSpecificFPKM\":{\"Glioma\":\"136.0\"},\"RN