\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"10.4\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"9.3\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"5.7\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"13.0\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"9.7\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"6.1\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"14.7\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"7.3\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"9.6\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"10.3\"}',NULL,'This gene encodes a member of the protein family comprised of both platelet-derived growth factors (PDGF) and vascular endothelial growth factors (VEGF). The encoded preproprotein is proteolytically processed to generate platelet-derived growth factor subunit B, which can homodimerize, or alternatively, heterodimerize with the related platelet-derived growth factor subunit A. These proteins bind and activate PDGF receptor tyrosine kinases, which play a role in a wide range of developmental processes. Mutations in this gene are associated with meningioma. Reciprocal translocations between chromosomes 22 and 17, at sites where this gene and that for collagen type 1, alpha 1 are located, are associated with dermatofibrosarcoma protuberans, a rare skin tumor. Alternative splicing results in multiple transcript variants. [provided by RefSeq, Oct 2015]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (48,'EGF','','epidermal growth factor',1950,'EGF_HUMAN','upstream','4q25',109912884,110012962,1,'','NM_001963','NP_001954','1,058,050,412,885,590,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','LOC103691699;Rattus norvegicus,Egf;Mus musculus,cue;Drosophila melanogaster,egf;Danio rerio,Egf;Rattus norvegicus','Древнейший общий предок metazoa имел комплементарный EGFR рецептор и предполагаемый лиганд EGF, которые дуплицировались или терялись в ходе эволюции [1].','EGF стимулирует рост различных эпидермальных и эпителиальных тканей in vivo и in vitro, а также некоторых фибробластов в клеточной культуре [2]. Активирует тирозин-кинзаную активность EGFR [3].','Прямые доказательства на не млекопитающих, Участие гена в связанных со старением процессах/механизмах','Активация EGF рецптора LET-23 у C. elegans ассоциирована с увеличенной средней и максимальной продолжительностью жизни [4]. EGF путь регулирует различные пути, влияющие на процесс старения клеток [5 - обзор].','The last common metazoan ancestor had an initial complement of one EGFR and one putative EGF ligand, which was often expanded or lost during animal evolution [1].','EGF stimulates the growth of various epidermal and epithelial tissues in vivo and in vitro and of some fibroblasts in cell culture [2]. Activates tyrosine-kinase domain of EGFR','Activation of EGF receptor LET-23 in C. elegnas is associated with increased mean and maximum lifespan [4]. EGF pathway regulates various pathways leading to cell senescence [5 - review].','[1] 10.1038/srep28071, [2] https://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P01133, [3] http://www.jbc.org/content/265/14/7709.long, [4] 10.1016/j.exger.2010.10.010, [5] 10.18632/aging.100384',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614757142,3,'','',6,'ENSG00000138798','{\"Gene\":\"EGF\",\"GeneSynonym\":[],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000138798\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Epidermal growth factor\",\"Uniprot\":[\"P01133\"],\"Chr