":\"0.0\",\"BloodRNANKCellNX\":\"0.0\",\"BloodRNANonClassicalMonocyteNX\":\"4.1\",\"BloodRNAPlasmacytoidDCNX\":\"0.0\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"0.0\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"0.6\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"8.3\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"9.1\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"4.6\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"10.4\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"8.2\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"3.9\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"7.9\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"8.1\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"7.7\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"6.7\"}',NULL,'The protein encoded by this gene is a cell surface tyrosine kinase receptor for members of the platelet-derived growth factor family. These growth factors are mitogens for cells of mesenchymal origin. The identity of the growth factor bound to a receptor monomer determines whether the functional receptor is a homodimer (PDGFB or PDGFD) or a heterodimer (PDGFA and PDGFB). This gene is essential for normal development of the cardiovascular system and aids in rearrangement of the actin cytoskeleton. This gene is flanked on chromosome 5 by the genes for granulocyte-macrophage colony-stimulating factor and macrophage-colony stimulating factor receptor; all three genes may be implicated in the 5-q syndrome. A translocation between chromosomes 5 and 12, that fuses this gene to that of the ETV6 gene, results in chronic myeloproliferative disorder with eosinophilia. [provided by RefSeq, Aug 2017]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (52,'EPOR','EPO-R','Erythropoietin receptor',2057,'EPOR_HUMAN','downstream','19p13.2',11377204,11384341,-1,'','NM_000121','NP_000112','94,356,351,094,384,200,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','Epor;Mus musculus,Epor;Rattus norvegicus,epor;Danio rerio','Эритропоэтиновый сигналинг возник до дивергенции позвоночных [1].','EpoR трансмембранный белок с единственным трансмембранным доменом. N-концевой домен содержит сайт связывания эритропоэтина, C-концевой домен содержит сайт связывания янус-киназы 2 (JAK2) [2]. Способствует эритропоэтин индуцированной пролиферации и дифференциации эритробластов [3].','Прямые доказательства на млекопитающих, Участие гена в связанных со старением процессах/механизмах','В модели старения крыс, индуцированной Д-галактозой, терапия эритропоэтином в течение недели смогла улучшить способность запоминания и обучения у стареющих крыс, предотвратить возрастные изменения гистологии гиппокампа [4] и повысить антиоксидантный статус [5]. Не было найдено отличий в экспрессии Эритропоэтина и его рецептора в различных возрастных группах крыс [6]. Новые исследования показывают роль эритропоэтина в индуцировании биогенеза митохондрий, что рассматривается как одно из направлений борьбы со старением [7, 8].','Erythropoietin signaling evolved before Vertebrate lineage divergence [1].','EpoR is a single span membrane protein. N-terminal extracellular domain contains erythropoietin binding sites, C-terminal intracellular domain has Janus kinase 2-binding sites [2]. Mediates erythropoietin-induced erythroblast proliferation and differentiation [3].','In D-galactose-induced rat aging model EPO, administered for 1 week can significantly improve learning and memory ability in aging rats and can provide protection against aging by improving the hippocampus morphology [4] and enhance antioxidant protection [5]. There is no difference in EPOR expression in different age groups of rats [6]. Recent articles point out the involvement of EPO signaling in inducing of mitochondria biogenesis, which could be a way for longevity [7, 8].','[1] 10.1016/bs.vh.2017.02.004, [2] 10.1016/bs.vh.2017.02.005, [3] 10.1016/bs.vh.2017.02.002, [4] 10.1007/s12031-017-0885-1, [5] https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23230737, [6] 10.3892/mmr.2016.6010, [7] 10.3892/mmr.2016.6010, [8] 10.3389/fgene.2019.00435',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614757228,3,'','',6,'ENSG00000187266','{\"Gene\":\"EPOR\",\"GeneSynonym\":[],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000187266\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Erythropoietin receptor\",\"Uniprot\":[\"P19235\"],\"Chromosome\":\"19\",\"Position\":\"11377205-11384342\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease related genes\",\"FDA approved drug targets\",\"Predicted membrane proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":null,\"MolecularFunction\":[\"Receptor\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Congenital erythrocytosis\",\"Disease mutation\",\"FDA approved drug targets\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Low tissue specificity\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":null,\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Low cell line specificity\",\"RNACellLineDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNACellLineSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNACellLineSpecificNX\":null,\"RNACancerSpecificity\":\"Low cancer specificity\",\"RNACancerDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNACancerSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNACancerSpecificFPKM\":null,\"RNABrainRegionalSpecificity\":\"Low region specificity\",\"RNABrainRegionalDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNABrainRegionalSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNABrainRegionalSpecificNX\":null,\"RNABloodCellSpecificity\":\"Low cell type specificity\",\"RNABloodCellDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNABloodCellSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNABloodCellSpecificNX\":n