onClassicalMonocyteNX\":\"10.5\",\"BloodRNAPlasmacytoidDCNX\":\"12.4\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"5.8\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"7.3\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"13.5\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"14.9\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"30.1\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"19.2\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"13.4\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"14.1\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"18.3\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"12.8\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"13.6\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"18.2\"}',NULL,'This gene encodes glucocorticoid receptor, which can function both as a transcription factor that binds to glucocorticoid response elements in the promoters of glucocorticoid responsive genes to activate their transcription, and as a regulator of other transcription factors. This receptor is typically found in the cytoplasm, but upon ligand binding, is transported into the nucleus. It is involved in inflammatory responses, cellular proliferation, and differentiation in target tissues. Mutations in this gene are associated with generalized glucocorticoid resistance. Alternative splicing of this gene results in transcript variants encoding either the same or different isoforms. Additional isoforms resulting from the use of alternate in-frame translation initiation sites have also been described, and shown to be functional, displaying diverse cytoplasm-to-nucleus trafficking patterns and distinct transcriptional activities (PMID:15866175). [provided by RefSeq, Feb 2011]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (76,'EGR1','TIS8 G0S30 NGFI-A KROX-24 ZIF-268 AT225 ZNF225','early growth response 1',1958,'EGR1_HUMAN','upstream','5q31.1',138465492,138469315,1,'','NM_001964','NP_001955','3,127,059,110,350,410,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','prz1;Schizosaccharomyces pombe,Egr1;Mus musculus,Egr1;Rattus norvegicus,egr1;Danio rerio,sr;Drosophila melanogaster,egrh-1;Caenorhabditis elegans,egrh-2;Caenorhabditis elegans,MIG2;Saccharomyces cerevisiae,MIG1;Saccharomyces cerevisiae,MIG3;Saccharomyces cerevisiae','EGR семейство факторов транскрипции найдено и изучено в пределах позвоночных [1, 2].','ДНК-связывающий фактор транскрипции с доменом цинковый палец. EGR1 играет роль в синаптической пластичности, включая процессы обучения и запоминания, зависимости, тревожности и психоневрологических заболеваний [3 - обзор].','Возрастные изменения экспрессии гена/активности белка у млекопитающих','Во время исследования новой клетки крысами экспрессия EGR1 в зубчатой извилине была значительно ниже у старых особей (24-32 месяца) по сравнению со взрослыми (9-12 месяцев). В привычной клетке разницы в экспрессии нет [4]. У старых крыс экспрессия EGR1 в слизистой желудка выше, чем у взрослых, что ведет к большей вероятности гастропатологий [5].','EGR family of transcription factors is found and studied within Vertebrates [1, 2].','zinc finger DNA-binding transcription factor. EGR1 plays its role in synaptic plasticity including learning and memory, addiction, anxiety, and neuropsychiatric disorders. [3 - review].','During exploring a new cage EGR1 expression in dental gyrus is significantly lower in aged (24-32 months) compared to adult (9-12 months). In undisturbed conditions, no difference in expression was seen [4]. In gastric mucosa of aged rats and humans EGR-1 is significantly upregulated leading to increased susceptibility to gastropathy [5].','[1] 10.1006/mpev.2000.0818, [2] 10.1016/j.ygcen.2017.01.020, [3] 10.3389/fnbeh.2017.00035, [4] 10.1002/hipo.22583, [5] 10.3748/wj