NAPlasmacytoidDCNX\":\"3.1\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"0.9\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"1.6\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"12.4\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"18.1\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"6.7\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"16.0\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"10.3\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"8.4\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"24.1\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"9.4\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"17.1\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"21.2\"}','','This gene is a protooncogene that encodes a protein tyrosine kinase involved in a variety of cellular processes, including cell division, adhesion, differentiation, and response to stress. The activity of the protein is negatively regulated by its SH3 domain, whereby deletion of the region encoding this domain results in an oncogene. The ubiquitously expressed protein has DNA-binding activity that is regulated by CDC2-mediated phosphorylation, suggesting a cell cycle function. This gene has been found fused to a variety of translocation partner genes in various leukemias, most notably the t(9;22) translocation that results in a fusion with the 5\' end of the breakpoint cluster region gene (BCR; MIM:151410). Alternative splicing of this gene results in two transcript variants, which contain alternative first exons that are spliced to the remaining common exons. [provided by RefSeq, Aug 2014]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (79,'BRCA2','FAD FAD1 BRCC2 XRCC11 FANCD1 FACD FANCD','breast cancer 2, early onset',675,'BRCA2_HUMAN','functional','13q12.3',32315480,32399672,1,'','NM_000059','NP_000050','93,531,771,261,915,400,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','Brca2;Mus musculus,Brca2;Rattus norvegicus,brca2;Danio rerio','Представитель семейства лигаз, участвующих в негомологичной репарации повреждений ДНК. BRCA1 гомологи найдены у растений и животных, также гомологи BRCA2 найдены у грибов [1], [2].','Унаследованные мутации BRCA1 и этого гена BRCA2 повышают риск развития рака груди или яичников на протяжении всей жизни. Как BRCA1, так и BRCA2 участвуют в поддержании стабильности генома, в частности, в пути гомологичной рекомбинации для репарации двухцепочечной ДНК. Самый большой экзон в обоих генах - это экзон 11, который несет в себе наиболее важные и частые мутации у пациентов с раком груди. Ген BRCA2 был обнаружен на хромосоме 13q12.3 человека. Белок BRCA2 содержит несколько копий мотива из 70 аминокислотных остатков, называемого мотивом BRC, и эти мотивы опосредуют связывание с рекомбиназой RAD51, которая участвует в репарации ДНК. BRCA2 считается геном-супрессором опухоли, поскольку опухоли с мутациями BRCA2 обычно проявляют потерю гетерозиготности (LOH) аллеля дикого типа. [предоставлено RefSeq, май 2020 г.]','Участие гена в связанных со старением процессах/механизмах','BRCA1/2 гомологи поддерживают стабильность генома путем репарации ДНК, а также повышают регенеративную способность клеток [4-6].  [4] 10.15252/embr.201540437 , [5] 10.1007/s12035-017-0574-7','Ligase family taking part in nonhomologous end joining. BRCA1 homologs are found in the plant and animal kingdoms while BRCA2 homologs are additionally found in the fungi kingdom [1], [2].','Inherited mutations in BRCA1 and this gene, BRCA2, confer increased lifetime risk of developing breast or ovarian cancer. Both BRCA1 and BRCA2 are involved in maintenance of genome stability, specifically the homologous recombination pathway for double-strand DNA repair. The largest exon in both genes is exon 11, which harbors the most important and frequent mutations in breast cancer patients. The BRCA2 gene was found on chromosome 13q12.3 in human. The BRCA2 protein contains several copies of a 70 aa motif called the BRC motif, and these motifs mediate binding to the RAD51 recombinase which functions in DNA repair. BRCA2 is considered a tumor suppressor gene, as tumors with BRCA2 mutations generally exhibit loss of heterozygosity (LOH) of the wild-type allele. [provided by RefSeq, May 2020]','BRCA1/2 homologues maintain genome stability through DNA repair and increasing regeneration ability of cells [4-6].','[1] 10.21873/cgp.20040, [2] 10.1093/annonc/mdv022',NULL,0,2,NULL,1616326297,2,'','',1,'ENSG00000139618','{\"Gene\":\"BRCA2\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"BRCC2\",\"FACD\",\"FAD\",\"FAD1\",\"FANCD\",\"FANCD1\",\"XRCC11\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000139618\",\"GeneDescription\":\"BRCA2, DNA repair associated\",\"Uniprot\":[\"P51587\"],\"Chromosome\":\"13\",\"Position\":\"32315474-32400266\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease related genes\",\"Predicted intracellular proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":[\"Cell cycle\",\"DNA damage\",\"DNA recombination\",\"DNA repair\"],\"MolecularFunction\":[\"DNA-binding\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease mutation\",\"Fanconi anemia\",\"Tumor suppressor\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at transcript level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Tissue enhanced\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":{\"LymphoidTissue\":\"23.2\",\"Testis\":\"16.9\"},\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Low cell line specificity\",\"RNACellLineDistribution\":\"Detected 