"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"0.1\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"1.0\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"0.9\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"0.4\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"1.2\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"0.8\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"0.6\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"0.8\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"0.3\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"0.9\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"0.4\"}',NULL,'The protein encoded by this gene is a transcriptional activator involved in cell proliferation. The encoded protein is phosphorylated in M phase and regulates the expression of several cell cycle genes, such as cyclin B1 and cyclin D1. Several transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for this gene. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2011]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (131,'COQ7','CLK-1 CAT5','coenzyme Q7 homolog, ubiquinone',10229,'COQ7_HUMAN','model','16p12.3',19067595,19080095,1,'','NM_016138','NP_057222','10,501,970,115,110,900,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','coq7;Schizosaccharomyces pombe,Coq7;Rattus norvegicus,Coq7;Mus musculus,COQ7;Drosophila melanogaster,clk-1;Caenorhabditis elegans,coq7;Danio rerio,CAT5;Saccharomyces cerevisiae','Фермент COQ7 описан у эукариот и бактерий, но не архей и участвует в синтезе убиквинона. Недавно отнесен к суперсемейтву ферритиноподобных белков [1].','У C. elegans и S. cerevisiae coq7/clk-1 необходим для биосинтеза коэнзима Q [2]. Исследование мутантов по coq7 на мышах, показали, что он необходим для поддержания целостности митохондрий и нейрогенеза [3].','Прямые доказательства на млекопитающих, Прямые доказательства на не млекопитающих','Продолжительность жизни C. elegans была увеличена на 60 процентов при исключении CoQ8 из рациона [4]. Трансгенная экспрессия COQ7 снизила увеличенную с помощью делеции clk1 продолжительность жизни мышей до уровня, сопоставимого с контрольными мышами дикого типа [5].','An enzyme known as COQ7 found in eukaryotes and bacteria but not archaea and involved in the biosynthesis of ubiquinone has recently been biochemically characterized as a member of the FLSF [1].','In C. elegans and Saccharomyces cerevisiae, coq7/clk-1 is required for the biosynthesis of coenzyme Q [2]. Mutant studies on mice show that COQ7 maintain mitochondrial integrity and neurogenesis [3].','C. elegans showed an extended lifespan by 60 percent when dietary CoQ8 was removed [4]. Transgenic expression of COQ7 reversed clk-1 induced extended lifespan in mice to the comparable level with wild-type control [5].','[1] 10.1016/j.bbagen.2010.05.010, [2] 10.1111/j.1474-9728.2004.00116.x, [3] 10.1006/bbrc.2001.5977, [4] 10.1126/science.1064653, [5] 10.1006/bbrc.2001.5439',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614756740,8,'','',7