his gene encodes a DNA topoisomerase, an enzyme that controls and alters the topologic states of DNA during transcription. This enzyme catalyzes the transient breaking and rejoining of a single strand of DNA which allows the strands to pass through one another, thus relaxing the supercoils and altering the topology of DNA. The enzyme interacts with DNA helicase SGS1 and plays a role in DNA recombination, cellular aging and maintenance of genome stability. Low expression of this gene may be related to higher survival rates in breast cancer patients. This gene has a pseudogene on chromosome 22. Alternate splicing results in multiple transcript variants. Additional alternatively spliced transcript variants of this gene have been described, but their full-length nature is not known. [provided by RefSeq, Aug 2013]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (148,'ERCC1','RAD10','excision repair cross-complementation group 1',2067,'ERCC1_HUMAN','mammal,functional','19q13.32',45413434,45423562,-1,'HS_ERCC1','NM_202001','NP_973730','9,197,240,819,717,470,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','swi10;Schizosaccharomyces pombe,Ercc1;Mus musculus,Ercc1;Drosophila melanogaster,ercc-1;Caenorhabditis elegans,Ercc1;Rattus norvegicus,RAD10;Saccharomyces cerevisiae,ercc1;Danio rerio','Человеческий ген репарации разрывов ДНК имеет ортолога у дрожжей. А также C-концевой домен имеет гомологию с белками репарации E.coli [1, 2].','ERCC1 и ERCC4 гены кодируют две субъединицы ERCC1-XPF нуклеазы. Этот фермент играет важную роль в реперации повреждений ДНК и поддрежании геномной стабильности [3].','Прямые доказательства на млекопитающих, Ассоциации гена с долголетием/фенотипом старения','ERCC1 мутантнтые мыши имеют значительно сокращенную продолжительность жизни [5] в 19 недель, которая может быть увеличена до 44 недель с помощью диетических ограничения [6]. Нарушенная система репарации ДНК увеличивает риск возрастной болезни Паркинсона у мышей [7].','Human excision repair genes are orthologs of one from yeasts and also C-terminal has some homology with E.coli repair genes [1, 2].','The ERCC1 and ERCC4 genes encode the two subunits of the ERCC1-XPF nuclease. This enzyme plays an important role in the repair of DNA damage and in maintaining genomic stability [3].','ERCC1 mutant mice have decreased lifespan [5] of 19 weeks (median age), which was extended by dietary restriction to median age of 44 weeks [6]. Disrupted DNA repair system increase the risk of age-induced Parkinson\'s disease in mice [7].','[1] 10.1093/nar/16.12.5305, [2] 10.1016/0092-8674(86)90014-0, [3] 10.1016/j.gene.2015.06.026, [4] 10.3390/molecules23123205, [5] 10.1007/s00401-010-0715-9, [6] 10.1042/CS20170026, [7] 10.1016/j.celrep.201