dRNAPlasmacytoidDCNX\":\"0.0\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"0.0\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"0.0\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"1.2\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"1.1\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"0.8\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"1.9\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"1.1\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"1.0\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"1.3\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"0.8\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"1.9\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"0.9\"}',NULL,'Prostaglandin-endoperoxide synthase (PTGS), also known as cyclooxygenase, is the key enzyme in prostaglandin biosynthesis, and acts both as a dioxygenase and as a peroxidase. There are two isozymes of PTGS: a constitutive PTGS1 and an inducible PTGS2, which differ in their regulation of expression and tissue distribution. This gene encodes the inducible isozyme. It is regulated by specific stimulatory events, suggesting that it is responsible for the prostanoid biosynthesis involved in inflammation and mitogenesis. [provided by RefSeq, Feb 2009]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (198,'HSPA8','HSC71 HSC70 HSP73 HSPA10','heat shock 70kDa protein 8',3312,'HSP7C_HUMAN','functional','11q24.1',123057492,123062335,-1,'HS_HSPA8','NM_006597','NP_006588','11,518,492,102,050,600,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','AABR07011951.1;Rattus norvegicus,Hspa8;Rattus norvegicus,Hspa8;Rattus norvegicus,Hspa8;Mus musculus,Hsc70-1;Drosophila melanogaster,Hsc70-4;Drosophila melanogaster,hsp-1;Caenorhabditis elegans,HSPA8 (1 of many);Danio rerio,hspa8;Danio rerio,LOC680121;Rattus norvegicus,SSA1;Saccharomyces cerevisiae','Семейство генов HSP70. Человеческие гены HSP70 произошли и дифференцировались от одного прокариотического предка неопределенного происхождения. Гены семейства HSP70 очень рано разошлись в эукариотической эволюции. Но функция не менялась от бактерий к человеку [1].','HSPA8 это молекулярный шаперон. Контролирует все аспекты клеточного протеостаза, такие как складывание растущей белковой цепи, импорт белка в органеллы, восстановление агрегировавших белков и сборка мультибелковых комплексов [2]. Он представляет собой конститутивно экспрессируемый родственный белок семейства HSP70, который участвует в клатрин-непокрытой АТФазе во время клатрин-опосредованного эндоцитоза, фолдинге белка, импорте белка в ER и митохондрии, клеточном транспорте органелл вдоль микротрубочек, играет важную роль в работе иммунной системы [3].','Участие гена в связанных со старением процессах/механизмах','Нарушение белкового гомеостаза (протеостаза), которое характеризуется появлением ненативных белковых агрегатов в различных тканях, характерно для старения и ряда заболеваний [4, 5].','HSP70 gene family. Human HSP70 genes originated and differentiated from a unique prokaryotic ancestor of uncertain identity. HSP70s have diverged very early in eukaryotic evolution. But the function has been retained from bacteria to humans [1].','HSPA8 is a molecular chaperone, which controls all aspects of cellular proteostasis such as nascent protein chain folding, protein import into organelles, recovering of proteins from aggregation, and assembly of multi-protein complexes [2]. It represents a constitutively expressed, cognate protein of the HSP70 family, which involved in a clathrin-uncoating ATPase during clathrin-mediated endocytosis, protein folding, protein import in ER and mitochondria, cellular transport of organelles along microtubules, plays important role in the immune system [3].','Loss of protein homeostasis (proteostasis) is a common feature of aging and disease that is characterized by the appearance of nonnative protein aggregates in various tissues [4–6].','[1] 10.1186/1471-2148-8-19,<br>[2] 10.1007/s12192-016-0676-6,<br>[3] 10.4161/auto.26448,<br>[4] 10.1146/annurev-biochem-060614-033955,<br>[5] 10.1007/s12079-014-0243-9,<br>[6] 10.1155/2012/919832',NULL,1,0,NULL,1616696025,8,'','',5,'ENSG00000109971','{\"Gene\":\"HSPA8\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"HSC70\",\"HSC71\",\"HSP73\",\"HSPA10\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000109971\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Heat shock protein family A (Hsp70) member 8\",\"Uniprot\":[\"P11142\"],\"Chromosome\":\"11\",\"Position\":\"123057489-123063230\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Plasma proteins\",\"Predicted intracellular proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":[\"Host-virus interaction\",\"mRNA processing\",\"mRNA splicing\",\"Stress response\",\"Transcription\",\"Transcription regulation\"],\"MolecularFunction\":[\"Chaperone\",\"Repressor\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Cancer-related genes\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Low tissue specificity\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":null,\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Low cell li