X\":\"54.4\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"113.9\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"177.2\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"24.2\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"32.3\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"19.6\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"33.4\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"21.8\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"17.1\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"19.9\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"19.9\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"19.3\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"19.4\"}',NULL,'The protein encoded by this gene is one of the three catalytic subunits of protein phosphatase 1 (PP1). PP1 is a serine/threonine specific protein phosphatase known to be involved in the regulation of a variety of cellular processes, such as cell division, glycogen metabolism, muscle contractility, protein synthesis, and HIV-1 viral transcription. Increased PP1 activity has been observed in the end stage of heart failure. Studies in both human and mice suggest that PP1 is an important regulator of cardiac function. Mouse studies also suggest that PP1 functions as a suppressor of learning and memory. Three alternatively spliced transcript variants encoding different isoforms have been found for this gene. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (227,'DBN1','D0S117E','drebrin 1',1627,'DREB_HUMAN','putative','5q35.3',177456613,177473693,-1,'','NM_004395','NP_004386','1,037,475,488,385,780,000,000,000,000,000','app1;Schizosaccharomyces pombe,Dbn1;Mus musculus,Dbn1;Rattus norvegicus,dbn1;Danio rerio','Дребрин относится к семейству актин-связывающих белков ADF-H, его ортологи найдены среди различных эукариот [1, 2].  During mouse brain development, Во время развития мозга модельных мышеи уровень экспрессии Dbn1 был навысшим к 14 дню развития эмбриона, постнатально ослаблялся, достигал своей наивысшей точки на 7 день после рождения (P7) и демонстрировал очень низкий уровень в зрелом возрасте.Данные результаты предполагают, что Dbn1 может играть ключевую роль в развитии мозга мыши и может регулировать дифференцировку NSC с помощью нитчатого актина.','Организатор актинового цитоскелета, который участвует в формировании клеточной формы [3]. Важен для развития мозга [4].','Возрастные изменения экспрессии гена/активности белка у млекопитающих, Участие гена в связанных со старением процессах/механизмах','Исследования показывают, что уровень экспрессии дребрина в гиппокампе мышей снижается по мере старения [5, 7], аналогичные результаты показаны на кошках [6]. Дополнительная стимуляция экспрессии дребрина у двухмесячных мышей с болезнью Альцгемймера, улучшила функцию памяти у этих мышей в старости [5].','Drebrin is a member of the actin-binding ADF-H domain, which orthologs are found among eukaryotes [1, 2].Dbn1 expression level was high at E14, attenuated postnatally, reached its highest point at postnatal day 7 (P7), and showed a very low level at adulthood [8].Imaging data showed that Dbn1 was mainly expressed in the hippocampus, ventricular zone, and cortex, where NSCs are densely distributed, and that the intracellular distribution of Dbn1 was predominantly located in the cytoplasm edges and neurites. Moreover, the signal for colocalization of Dbn1 with actin was intense at E14, P0, and P7, but it was weak at adulthood. During NSC differentiation, Dbn1 mRNA expression increased after the onset of differentiation and reached its highest point at 3days, followed by a decrease in expression. The imaging data showed that Dbn1 was increasingly expressed in the extending neurites in accordance with the cell morphological changes that occur during differentiation. ','Actin cytoskeleton-organizing protein that plays a role in the formation of cell projections [3]. Crucial for brain development [4].','It was shown that drebrin expression in the hippocampus is declined during aging in mice [5, 7] and cats [6]. Stimulation of drebrin expression in 2-months-old AD mice improved their memory ability at their aging [5].','[1] 10.1002/cm.20530, [2] 10.1007/978-4-431-56550-5_2, [3] 10.1242/jcs.064238, [4] 10.1007/978-4-431-56550-5_2, [5] 10.1111/cns.12706, [6] 10.1016/0168-0102(92)90032-8, [7] 10.1016/j.neuroscience.2016.03.015 [8] DOI: 10.1016/j.bbrc.2014.04.152\r\n',NULL,1,3,NULL,1623140182,2,' Явные сигналы колокализации Dbn1 с актином были обнаружены в нейритах и ​​дендритных шипах.','Furthermore, obvious colocalization signals of Dbn1 with actin were found in the neurites and dendritic spines.',6,'ENSG00000113758','{\"Gene\":\"DBN1\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"D0S117E\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000113758\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Drebrin 1\",\"Uniprot\":[\"Q16643\"],\"Chromosome\":\"5\",\"Position\":\"177456608-177474401\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Plasma proteins\",\"Predicted intracellular proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":[\"Differentiation\",\"Neurogenesis\"],\"MolecularFunction\":[\"Actin-binding\",\"Developmental protein\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Alzheimer disease\",\"Amyloidosis\",\"Neurodegeneration\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Low tissu