ppocampalFormationNX\":\"7.7\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"4.4\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"10.3\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"4.6\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"8.8\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"12.5\"}',NULL,'The protein encoded by this gene is a member of the PP2C family of Ser/Thr protein phosphatases. PP2C family members are known to be negative regulators of cell stress response pathways. The expression of this gene is induced in a p53-dependent manner in response to various environmental stresses. While being induced by tumor suppressor protein TP53/p53, this phosphatase negatively regulates the activity of p38 MAP kinase, MAPK/p38, through which it reduces the phosphorylation of p53, and in turn suppresses p53-mediated transcription and apoptosis. This phosphatase thus mediates a feedback regulation of p38-p53 signaling that contributes to growth inhibition and the suppression of stress induced apoptosis. This gene is located in a chromosomal region known to be amplified in breast cancer. The amplification of this gene has been detected in both breast cancer cell line and primary breast tumors, which suggests a role of this gene in cancer development. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (246,'CHEK2','CDS1 CHK2 HuCds1 PP1425 bA444G7 RAD53','checkpoint kinase 2',11200,'CHK2_HUMAN','functional','22q12.1',28687743,28741834,-1,'','NM_001005735','NP_001005735','16,652,371,166,759,500,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','cds1;Schizosaccharomyces pombe,lok;Drosophila melanogaster,Chek2;Mus musculus,Chek2;Rattus norvegicus,chk-2;Caenorhabditis elegans,T08D2.7;Caenorhabditis elegans,chek2;Danio rerio,RAD53;Saccharomyces cerevisiae','Общая структура chk2 протеинов консервативна для всех эукариот [1].','Серин/треонин протеин киназа, необходимая для остановки клеточного цикла в контрольных точках (check points), активации репарации ДНК, апоптоза в ответ на двухцепочечное повреждение ДНК. Также может регулировать нормальное прохождение клеточного цикла [2, 3 - обзоры функций].','Прямые доказательства на не млекопитающих, Прямые доказательства на культурах клеток, Ассоциации гена с долголетием/фенотипом старения','Основной механизм влияния chk2 на старение - изменение ответа на повреждение ДНК. Делеция chk2 в кишечных стволовых клетках дрозофил вызывает раннее старение этих клеток [4]. Отсутствие chk2  позволяет brca1 дефицитным мышам избежать смерти в период эмбрионального развития, но эти мыши проявляют ранние признаки старения в возрасте 18 месяцев [5]. Дефицит chk2 снижает смертность и ранние признаки старения, вызванные Trf1-/- и T.','The overall structure of the Chk2 proteins is similar in all eukaryotes [1].','Serine/threonine-protein kinase which is required for checkpoint-mediated cell cycle arrest, activation of DNA repair and apoptosis in response to the presence of DNA double-strand breaks. May also negatively regulate cell cycle progression during unperturbed cell cycles [2,3 review on functions].','The main mechanism of influence on aging is via alteration of DNA-damage response. Deletion of chk2 induces premature aging of Drosophila intestinal stem cells [4]. Loss of CHEK2 enables mice lacking BRCA1 to avoid embryonic lethality but they are showing signs of premature aging at about 18 months of age [5]. Deficiency in chk2 rescues Trf1-/- or Terc-/- lethality and premature aging in mouse [6].','[1] 10.1038/35103059, [2] 10.1016/S1535-6108(03)00110-7, [3] 10.1016/j.dnarep.2004.03.033, [4] 10.18632/aging.101390., [5]  10.1038/sj.emboj.7601115, [6] 10.1111/acel.12237',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614756562,2,'','',7,'ENSG00000183765','{\"Gene\":\"CHEK2\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"bA444G7\",\"CDS1\",\"CHK2\",\"HuCds1\",\"PP1425\",\"RAD53\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000183765\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Checkpoint kinase 2\",\"Uniprot\":[\"O96017\"],\"Chromosome\":\"22\",\"Position\":\"28687743-28742422\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease related genes\",\"Enzymes\",\"Plasma proteins\",\"Potential drug targets\",\"Predicted intracellular proteins\",\"Predicted membrane proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":[\"Apoptosis\",\"Cell cycle\",\"Cell division\",\"DNA damage\",\"DNA repair\",\"Mitosis\",\"Transcription\",\"Transcription regulation\"],\"MolecularFunction\":[\"Kinase\",\"Serine/threonine-protein kinase\",\"Transferase\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Cancer-related genes\",\"Disease mutation\",\"Li-Fraumeni syndrome\",\"Tumor suppressor\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Low tissue specificity\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":null,\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Low cell line specificity\",\"RNACellLineDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNACellLineSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNACellLineSpecificNX\":null,\"RNACancerSpecificity\":\"Low cancer specificity\",\"RNACancerDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNACancerSpecificityScore\