s gene is a main control point for the regulation of gluconeogenesis. The cytosolic enzyme encoded by this gene, along with GTP, catalyzes the formation of phosphoenolpyruvate from oxaloacetate, with the release of carbon dioxide and GDP. The expression of this gene can be regulated by insulin, glucocorticoids, glucagon, cAMP, and diet. Defects in this gene are a cause of cytosolic phosphoenolpyruvate carboxykinase deficiency. A mitochondrial isozyme of the encoded protein also has been characterized. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (248,'ARHGAP1','RhoGAP p50rhoGAP CDC42GAP Cdc42GAP','Rho GTPase activating protein 1',392,'RHG01_HUMAN','mammal','11p11.2',46677075,46700665,-1,'','NM_004308','NP_004299','17227869','RhoGAP68F;Drosophila melanogaster,rga-1;Caenorhabditis elegans,Arhgap1;Mus musculus,Arhgap1;Rattus norvegicus,arhgap1;Danio rerio','Принадлежит к древнему суперсемейству белков, ARHGAP1 имеет общие для семейства свойства, но найден только в геноме человека [1].','Активирует ГТФ-азную функцию для Rho, Rac, Cdc42 белков, изменяя их в форму, предположительно не связывающуюся с ГДФ [1]. Регулирует клеточный цикл, реорганизует цитоскелет, влияет на полярность клеток. миграцию и инвазивность [2, 3, 4]. Регулирует эпителиально-мезенхимный переход [5].',NULL,'Дефицит ARHGAP1 у мышей вызывает сокращение продолжительности жизни на 12 месяцев и раннее развитие признаков старения. Вероятно, участвует в процессах старения у млекопитиающих [6].','ARHGAP1 is a member of the ancient superfamily, but ARHGAP1 found only in human [1].','GTPase activator for the Rho, Rac and Cdc42 proteins, converting them to the putatively inactive GDP-bound state [1]. Plays role in cell cycle progression, cytoskeletal reorganization, cell polarity, migration and invasion [2, 3, 4]. Regulates Epithelial-to-mesenchymal transitions [5].','Deficiency of ARHGAP1 in mice results in a short lifespan of about 12 months and the development of multiple premature aging-like phenotypes, suggesting that this gene may play a role in mammalian aging [6].','[1] 10.1042/BC20060086, [2] 10.1038/nature01148, [3] 10.1016/j.gene.2004.01.025, [4] 10.1016/S0962-8924(01)02153-5, [5] 10.1242/dev.095448, [6] 10.1073/pnas.0609149104',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614619423,2,'','',7,'ENSG00000175220','{\"Gene\":\"ARHGAP1\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"CDC42GAP\",\"p50rhoGAP\",\"RhoGAP\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000175220\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Rho GTPase activating protein 1\",\"Uniprot\":[\"Q07960\"],\"Chromosome\":\"11\",\"Position\":\"46677080-46