musNX\":\"1.2\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"0.5\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"0.0\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"3.2\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"0.3\"}',NULL,'This gene encodes a member of the p53 family of transcription factors involved in cellular responses to stress and development. It maps to a region on chromosome 1p36 that is frequently deleted in neuroblastoma and other tumors, and thought to contain multiple tumor suppressor genes. The demonstration that this gene is monoallelically expressed (likely from the maternal allele), supports the notion that it is a candidate gene for neuroblastoma. Many transcript variants resulting from alternative splicing and/or use of alternate promoters have been found for this gene, but the biological validity and the full-length nature of some variants have not been determined. [provided by RefSeq, Feb 2011]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (280,'CNR1','CB1K5 CB-R CB1 CANN6 CB1A CNR','cannabinoid receptor 1 (brain)',1268,'CNR1_HUMAN','putative','6q14-q15',88139865,88166048,-1,'','NM_001160226','NP_001153698','216,903,451,954,771,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000,000','Cnr1;Mus musculus,Cnr1;Rattus norvegicus,cnr1;Danio rerio','Первичноротые беспозвоночные, такие как дрозофилы и C.elegans не имеют ортологов CB1, что свидетельствует о появлении этого гены после дивергенции вторичноротых [1].','CB1 каннабиноидный рецептор — это связанный с G-протеином, который повсеместно экспрессируется в мозге. Эндоканнабиноиды и рецептор регулируют ретроградное ингибирование выделения нейротрансмитеров в мозге [2]. Эндоканнабиноидная система играет важнейшую роль в энергетическом балансе, проницаемости кишечника и иммуннитете [3]. В печени активация эндоканнабиноидами приводит к усилению липогенеза и снижению катаболизма жирных кислот. Эндоканнабиноиды способствуют резистентности к инсулину посредством активации периферических рецепторов CB1 [4].','Возрастные изменения экспрессии гена/активности белка у млекопитающих, Участие гена в связанных со старением процессах/механизмах','Экспрессия CB1 снижается во время старения у крыс [5]. Римонабант (CB1 обратный агонист) улучшил толерантрость к глюкозе и увеличил чувствительность скелетных мышц и печени к инсулину у пожилых крыс [6].','Protostomian invertebrates Drosophila melanogaster and Caenorhabditis elegans do not contain CB1 orthologues, indicating that CB1–like cannabinoid receptors may have evolved after the divergence of deuterostomes [1].','The CB1 cannabinoid receptor is a G protein-coupled receptor that is widely expressed throughout the brain. The endogenous ligands for the CB1 receptor (endocannabinoids) are N-arachidonylethanolamine and 2-arachidonoylglycerol; together the endocannabinoids and CB1R subserve activity-dependent, retrograde inhibition of neurotransmitter release in the brain [2]. The endocannabinoid system plays vital roles in the control of energy balance, the control of intestinal permeability and immunity [3]. In the liver, activation by endocannabinoids leads to increased de novo lipogenesis and reduced fatty acid catabolism. Endocannabinoids contribute to insulin resistance through activation of peripheral CB1 receptors [4].','Aging decreases CB1 expression in rats [5]. Rimonabant (CB1 inverse agonist) was shown to improve glucose tolerance and enhance skeletal muscle and liver insulin sensitivity in aged mice [6].','[1] 10.1098/rstb.2000.0787, [2] 10.1016/j.smim.2014.04.001, [3] 10.1016/j.bbi.2012.01.004, [4] 10.1038/nm.3265, [5] 10.1016/j.exger.2014.04.008, [6] 10.1111/acel.12438',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614756714,9,'','',6,'ENSG00000118432','{\"Gene\":\"CNR1\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"CANN6\",\"CB-R\",\"CB1\",\"CB1A\",\"CB1K5\",\"CNR\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000118432\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Cannabinoid receptor 1\",\"Uniprot\":[\"P21554\"],\"Chromosome\":\"6\",\"Position\":\"88139864-88166359\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Disease related genes\",\"FDA approved drug targets\",\"G-protein coupled receptors\",\"Predicted intracellular proteins\",\"Predicted membrane proteins\",\"Transporters\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":null,\"MolecularFunction\":[\"G-protein coupled receptor\",\"Receptor\",\"Transducer\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"FDA approved drug targets\",\"Obesity\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Tissue enhanced\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":{\"Brain\":\"30.5\"},\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Group enriched\",\"RNACellLineDistribution\":\"Detected in some\",\"RNACellLineSpecificityScore\":\"7\",\"RNACellLineSpecificNX\":{\"ASCDiff\":\"39.4\",\"HSkMC\":\"26.0\"},\"RNACancerSpecificity\":\"Can