NX\":\"38.3\",\"BloodRNANonClassicalMonocyteNX\":\"14.6\",\"BloodRNAPlasmacytoidDCNX\":\"42.5\",\"BloodRNATRegNX\":\"48.3\",\"BloodRNATotalPBMCNX\":\"66.0\",\"BrainRNAAmygdalaNX\":\"43.9\",\"BrainRNABasalGangliaNX\":\"39.9\",\"BrainRNACerebellumNX\":\"19.0\",\"BrainRNACerebralCortexNX\":\"66.1\",\"BrainRNAHippocampalFormationNX\":\"42.8\",\"BrainRNAHypothalamusNX\":\"40.3\",\"BrainRNAMidbrainNX\":\"33.5\",\"BrainRNAOlfactoryRegionNX\":\"43.7\",\"BrainRNAPonsAndMedullaNX\":\"45.2\",\"BrainRNAThalamusNX\":\"19.2\"}',NULL,'This gene encodes a lymphokine involved in cell-mediated immunity, immunoregulation, and inflammation. It plays a role in the regulation of macrophage function in host defense through the suppression of anti-inflammatory effects of glucocorticoids. This lymphokine and the JAB1 protein form a complex in the cytosol near the peripheral plasma membrane, which may indicate an additional role in integrin signaling pathways. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008]');
INSERT INTO `gene` VALUES (289,'DGAT1','ARGP1 DGAT','diacylglycerol O-acyltransferase 1',8694,'DGAT1_HUMAN','mammal','8q24.3',144314583,144326919,-1,'','NM_012079','NP_036211','222,911,641,967,513,000,000,000','are1;Schizosaccharomyces pombe,Dgat1;Mus musculus,mdy;Drosophila melanogaster,Dgat1;Rattus norvegicus,mboa-2;Caenorhabditis elegans,dgat1a;Danio rerio,dgat1b;Danio rerio,ARE1;Saccharomyces cerevisiae,ARE2;Saccharomyces cerevisiae','DGAT — это трансмембранный белок, который осуществляет финальную реакцию синтеза триглицеридов. DGAT1 распространены в пределах эукариот и идентифицированы в основных группах эукариот [1].','Катализирует терминальную стадию синтеза триацилглицерина с использованием диацилглицерина и жирного ацил-КоА в качестве субстратов. Может участвовать в сборке липопротеинов очень низкой плотности. В печени играет роль в превращении экзогенных жирных кислот в глицерин. Функционирует как основная ацил-КоА-ретинолацилтрансфераза в коже, где поддерживает ретиноидный гомеостаз и предотвращает токсическое действие ретиноидов, приводящее заболеваниям кожи и волос [2, 3].','Прямые доказательства на млекопитающих','Дефицит DGAT1 защитил самок мышей от возрастного накопления жира, накопления триглицеридов и воспалительных процессов в белой адипозной ткани, а также привел к увеличению средней и максимальной продолжительности жизни на 25 и 10 процентов соответственно [4]. Однако, кардиоспецифичный нокаут DGAT1 у мышей привел к ранней смерти (9 месяцев) 50 процентов животных [5].','DGAT is a transmembrane enzyme that acts in the final and committed step of TAG synthesis. DGAT1 genes are nearly ubiquitous in eukaryotes and are readily identifiable in all the major eukaryotic groups [1].','Catalyzes the terminal and only committed step in triacylglycerol synthesis by using diacylglycerol and fatty acyl CoA as substrates. In contrast to DGAT2 it is not essential for survival. May be involved in VLDL (very low-density lipoprotein) assembly. In the liver, plays a role in esterifying exogenous fatty acids to glycerol. Functions as the major acyl-CoA retinol acyltransferase (ARAT) in the skin, where it acts to maintain retinoid homeostasis and prevent retinoid toxicity leading to skin and hair disorders [2, 3].','Female DGAT1-deficient mice were protected from age-related increases in body fat, tissue triglycerides, and inflammation in white adipose tissue. This protection was accompanied by increased mean and maximal life spans of 25 percent and 10 percent [4]. Cardiomyocyte specific DGAT1 knockout in mice leads to premature death (9 months) of 50 percent of tested animals [5].','[1] 10.1186/1471-2148-11-263, [2] 10.1074/jbc.273.41.26765, [3] 10.1016/j.bbalip.2005.09.003, [4] 10.18632/aging.100424, [5] 10.1074/jbc.M114.601864 ',NULL,1,0,NULL,1614756915,2,'','',5,'ENSG00000185000','{\"Gene\":\"DGAT1\",\"GeneSynonym\":[\"ARGP1\",\"DGAT\"],\"Ensembl\":\"ENSG00000185000\",\"GeneDescription\":\"Diacylglycerol O-acyltransferase 1\",\"Uniprot\":[\"O75907\"],\"Chromosome\":\"8\",\"Position\":\"144314584-144326910\",\"ProteinClass\":[\"Disease related genes\",\"Enzymes\",\"Potential drug targets\",\"Predicted membrane proteins\"],\"BiologicalProcess\":null,\"MolecularFunction\":[\"Acyltransferase\",\"Transferase\"],\"DiseaseInvolvement\":[\"Disease mutation\"],\"Evidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"HPAEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"UniProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"NeXtProtEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"MSEvidence\":\"Evidence at protein level\",\"RNATissueSpecificity\":\"Tissue enriched\",\"RNATissueDistribution\":\"Detected in all\",\"RNATissueSpecificityScore\":\"9\",\"RNATissueSpecificNX\":{\"Intestine\":\"161.0\"},\"RNACellLineSpecificity\":\"Cell line enhanced\",\"RNACellLineDistribution\":\"Detected in many\",\"RNACellLineSpecificityScore\":null,\"RNACellLineSpecificNX\":{\"HepG2\":\"15.8\",\"PC3\":\"17.6\"},\"RNACancerSpecificity\":\"Low cancer specificity\",\"RNACancerDistribut